---
import PokerLayout from '../layouts/PokerLayout.astro';
---
<PokerLayout
  title="Accessibility — ChipShot Poker"
  description="Accessibility notes for the ChipShot Poker concept site and its playable games."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-12 pb-20">
    <span class="eyebrow">A11y</span>
    <h1 class="display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-parchment mt-3">Accessibility</h1>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-5 mb-6"></div>

    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      ChipShot Poker is a concept demo with four playable card games &mdash; Texas Hold&rsquo;em,
      Blackjack, Five Card Draw, and Video Poker. No real money, no accounts, no tracking.
      The chip stacks are pretend, but the accessibility work is real.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Keyboard &amp; focus</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      Every game is fully playable from the keyboard. Tab moves through the action
      buttons (Deal, Hit, Stand, Bet, Draw, etc.) in reading order, and Enter or Space
      activates the focused control. Focus rings are rendered in gold so they stay
      visible on the dark felt. A skip link jumps past the header on every page.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Screen readers</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      Game status &mdash; hand results, bankroll changes, dealer actions &mdash; is
      announced through ARIA live regions (<code class="text-gold-bright">aria-live="polite"</code>)
      so a screen reader hears "Dealer busts. You win $50." without the user hunting
      for the update. Cards carry descriptive labels (e.g. "Ace of spades"), and
      decorative chip art is hidden with <code class="text-gold-bright">aria-hidden</code>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Color &amp; contrast</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      The dark felt theme is built around gold <code class="text-gold-bright">#d4af37</code>
      on felt <code class="text-gold-bright">#082619</code>, which measures roughly
      <strong>8.5:1</strong> &mdash; comfortably above WCAG AA (4.5:1) and clearing
      AAA for normal text. Parchment body copy and red/black card pips were tuned
      to the same standard.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Motion &amp; sound</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      Card dealing and flip animations (<code class="text-gold-bright">.cs-card--dealt</code>,
      <code class="text-gold-bright">.cs-card--flip</code>) honor
      <code class="text-gold-bright">prefers-reduced-motion</code> &mdash; cards
      appear in place instead of sliding. Chip clinks, riffles, and win stings can
      be silenced with the mute toggle in the header; the preference is remembered
      across visits.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Privacy</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      Bankroll, hand history, and the mute setting live in
      <code class="text-gold-bright">localStorage</code> only. No analytics, no
      tracking cookies, no third-party scripts following you between games.
      Clearing site data resets everything.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-xl text-parchment mt-10">Testing</h2>
    <div class="gold-rule mt-3 mb-4 opacity-60"></div>
    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed">
      Every page runs an <a class="text-gold-bright underline" href="https://github.com/dequelabs/axe-core">axe-core</a>
      audit on load in development mode, and the game pages are spot-checked with
      VoiceOver on macOS and keyboard-only navigation before each release.
    </p>

    <p class="text-parchment-soft leading-relaxed mt-10">
      Spot a real-world issue? &mdash;
      <a class="text-gold-bright underline" href="mailto:hello@dcrader.dev">hello@dcrader.dev</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</PokerLayout>
